Based on my EDA, it seems that there are a good amount of variables that can influence win rate, namely operator, skillrank, mapname/objective_location and role, nbkills, and isdead.

Fitting Models

Now lets move onto fitting models.

set.seed(1121)
rainbow_split <- initial_split(data1, strata = "skillrank", prop = 0.75)

rainbow_train <- training(rainbow_split)
rainbow_test <- testing(rainbow_split)

rainbow_fold <- vfold_cv(rainbow_train, v = 10)
rainbow_recipe <- recipe(haswon ~ ., data = rainbow_train) %>% 
  step_dummy(all_nominal_predictors()) %>%
  # step_rm(endroundreason) %>% this says the column doesnt exist
  step_normalize(all_numeric_predictors())

prep(rainbow_recipe) %>% bake(new_data = rainbow_train)

knn_model <- nearest_neighbor(neighbors=10) %>% # tune n
  set_engine("kknn") %>% 
  set_mode("classification")

rainbow_knn_wflow <- workflow() %>%
  add_model(knn_model) %>%
  add_recipe(rainbow_recipe)

rainbow_fit_knn <- fit(rainbow_knn_wflow, rainbow_train)
log_reg_rainbow <- logistic_reg() %>%
  set_mode("classification") %>%
  set_engine("glm")

rainbow_log_wflow <- workflow() %>% 
  add_recipe(rainbow_recipe) %>% 
  add_model(log_reg_rainbow)

rainbow_fit_log <- fit(rainbow_log_wflow, data = rainbow_train)
rainbow_log_acc <- predict(rainbow_fit_log, new_data = rainbow_train, type = "class") %>% 
  bind_cols(rainbow_train %>% select(haswon)) %>% 
  accuracy(truth = haswon, estimate = .pred_class)

en_spec_churn <- logistic_reg(mixture = tune(), 
                              penalty = tune()) %>%
  set_mode("classification") %>%
  set_engine("glmnet")

en_workflow_churn <- workflow() %>% 
  add_recipe(churn_recipe) %>% 
  add_model(en_spec_churn)

en_grid <- grid_regular(penalty(range = c(0, 1),
                                     trans = identity_trans()),
                        mixture(range = c(0, 1)),
                             levels = 10)

tune_res_churn <- tune_grid(
  en_workflow_churn,
  resamples = mlc_fold, 
  grid = en_grid
)

autoplot(tune_res_churn)

collect_metrics(tune_res_churn)

best_en_churn <- select_by_one_std_err(tune_res_churn,
                          metric = "roc_auc",
                          penalty,
                          mixture
                          )

best_en_churn1 <- select_best(tune_res_churn,
                          metric = "roc_auc",
                          penalty,
                          mixture
                          )

en_final_churn <- finalize_workflow(en_workflow_churn,
                                      best_en_churn)

en_final_churn <- fit(en_final_churn, 
                        data = mlc_train)

augment(en_final_churn, new_data = mlc_train) %>%
  roc_auc(churn, .pred_yes)
